President Donald J. Trump issued a Presidential Memorandum recognizing and honoring the sacrifices made by military families on Gold Star Mother's and Family's Day. The memorandum acknowledges the bravery and dedication of the men and women in the Armed Forces, as well as the strength and resilience of their families. It highlights the importance of supporting and respecting Gold Star Families for their service and the work they do to preserve the memory of fallen heroes. The memorandum also calls upon government officials and the American people to display the flag and hold appropriate ceremonies to express gratitude and respect for Gold Star Mothers and Families.